node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 18, 2021. May be an image of 3 people, child, people standing and text that says 'This single mom is is braiding kids' hair for free to to help other struggling parents CNN'.

node.text:
Brittany Starks knows what it's like to struggle. Despite being a single mother who lives paycheck to paycheck and has been homeless twice, Starks hasn't allowed her hardships to break her spirit. She posted on Facebook that she'll braid kid's hair for free, so they can go back to school feeling happy and confident. She was flooded with requests and has already braided the hair of more than 35 children. Each appointment takes between four to six hours.⁠
⁠
"I wanted to do something for the parents like me whose money is going to feeding their children and making sure they have a roof over their head," Starks told CNN. "I wasn't expecting a big reaction. I thought I'd maybe get five kids or so, but I didn't realize how huge the need was for this."⁠
⁠
(📸: Raven Starks)

The number of migrants waiting to be processing by immigration agents swelled from roughly 400 one week ago to more than 12,000 on Friday.

node.text:
Habitual users of cannabis, including teens, are showing up in emergency rooms complaining of severe intestinal distress. “They vomit and then just continue to vomit whatever they have in their stomach, which can go on for hours,” said Dr. Sam Wang, a pediatric emergency medicine specialist and toxicologist at Children’s Hospital Colorado. “They often say they took a scalding hot shower before they came to the ER but it didn’t help.” This bizarre condition is called cannabis hyperemesis syndrome, or CHS.⁠
⁠

Tom Brady has already cemented his legacy as one of the greatest to ever play the game and the legendary quarterback says he's got many more years left in him. He was asked a question that people often search on Google: "Can Tom Brady play until 50 years old?" Brady replied: "I don't find it so difficult. Plus, in Florida, it's kind of a retiree state, so I feel like I can play and then just glide into retirement. I think I can. I think it's a yes."⁠
⁠
(📸: AP Images)⁠

node.text:
Vaccine advisers to the FDA have voted unanimously to recommend emergency use authorization of a booster dose of Pfizer’s vaccine six months after full vaccination in people 65 and older and those at high risk of severe Covid-19. The advisers also rejected a broader application to approve the use of booster doses of Pfizer’s vaccines in everyone 16 and older six months after they are fully vaccinated.⁠
⁠
(📸: Ting Shen/Xinhua/Getty Images)

node.text:
A US military investigation into a deadly Kabul drone strike in August has found that it killed 10 civilians and the driver, and the vehicle targeted was likely not a threat associated with ISIS-K, Gen. Frank McKenzie, the top general of US Central Command announced Friday.⁠
⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 17, 2021. May be an image of tree, outdoors and text that says 'Officials wrapped the world's largest tree in foil to guard it against California wildfires CNN GENERAL SHERMAN'.

node.text:
The world's largest tree has been wrapped in foil to protect it against flames from a fire raging in California's scenic Sequoia National Park. The tree, called General Sherman, is 275 feet tall, and over 36 feet in diameter at the base, making it taller than the Statue of Liberty from its base to the torch.⁠
⁠
(📸: Sequoia and Kings Canyon National Parks)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 17, 2021. May be an image of 3 people, people standing, suit and text that says 'Colorado governor weds his partner in the first same-sex marriage for a sitting governor CNN'.

node.text:
Colorado Gov. Jared Polis and his partner of 18 years, Marlon Reis, were married on Wednesday, according to a statement from the governor's office. In 2018, Polis became the first openly gay man elected governor in the United States. He is the second out LGBTQ person elected governor, after Oregon Gov. Kate Brown, according to the LGBTQ Victory Fund.⁠
⁠
(📸: Jocelyn Augustino/AP)
